TITLE: Using Tab Bar Icons in React Navigation Bottom Tabs
DESCRIPTION: This example shows different ways to specify tab bar icons, including local images, SVGs, SF Symbols (for Apple platforms), and remote image URLs.
SOURCE: https://github.com/callstackincubator/react-native-bottom-tabs/blob/main/docs/docs/docs/guides/usage-with-react-navigation.mdx#2025-04-20_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
<Tab.Screen
  name="Albums"
  component={Albums}
  options={{
    tabBarIcon: () => require('person.png'),
    // SVG is also supported
    tabBarIcon: () => require('person.svg'),
    // or
    tabBarIcon: () => ({ sfSymbol: 'person' }),
    // You can also pass a URL
    tabBarIcon: () => ({ uri: 'https://example.com/icon.png' }),
  }}
/>
```

